# AI Frontend Component Guidelines

When building AI-related UI components for OpenCut AI, follow these patterns.

## Component Location

All AI components go in `apps/web/src/components/editor/ai/` and are re-exported via `index.ts`.

## Design Principles

- **Distinctive, not generic** — avoid cookie-cutter AI aesthetics (purple gradients, Inter font, generic card layouts)
- **Production-grade** — real working code with polished micro-interactions
- **Cohesive** — match OpenCut's existing dark editor theme
- **Accessible** — keyboard navigation, focus states, screen reader support
- Use **shadcn/ui** primitives (Dialog, ScrollArea, Tooltip, ContextMenu, etc.)
- Use **cn()** for all className composition — never template literals
- Use **CSS variables** for theming consistency
- Use **Motion** library (framer-motion) for React animations

## AI Component Patterns

### Status Indicators
- Green dot = backend connected, Red dot = disconnected
- Poll `/health` every 30s via `use-ai-status.ts` hook
- Memory/GPU status bar via `GET /api/system/memory`

### Streaming/Progress
- Use WebSocket for long operations (transcription, generation)
- Show incremental results (segments appearing one by one)
- Always show cancel button for long-running operations

### Action Preview (Command Panel)
- LLM returns structured `EditorAction[]` — NEVER auto-apply
- Show preview cards with "Apply" / "Cancel" buttons
- User must confirm before actions modify timeline

### Transcript Panel (Lexical)
- Custom `TranscriptWordNode` with `{ start, end, confidence }` metadata
- Click word → seek video to timestamp
- Playback highlights active word
- Low confidence (< 0.7) = lighter color
- Filler words = subtle background highlight

## State Management

- AI state: `stores/ai-store.ts`
- Transcript state: `stores/transcript-store.ts`
- Access stores directly in sub-components — don't pass store values as props
- Use selectors for frequently-updating values

## Hooks

| Hook | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `use-ai-status` | Polls AI backend health |
| `use-ai-command` | Sends natural language commands to LLM |
| `use-transcription` | Triggers transcription, populates store |
| `use-transcription-stream` | WebSocket streaming for transcription progress |

## Types

All AI types in `types/ai.ts`:
- `TranscriptionSegment`, `TranscriptionWord`, `TranscriptionResult`
- `ImageGenParams`, `LLMCommandResult`, `EditorAction`
- `TTSRequest`, `AudioDenoiseRequest`
